{#
  Digi EX50 DAL config delta — flat-cutover (Checkpoint C) posture.

  Rendered by ansible/playbooks/configure-ex50.yml and piped into the DAL
  Admin CLI over SSH (mode 2: multi-line stdin). The session enters config
  mode, stages the assignments below, then `save` commits them atomically and
  `exit` leaves. See docs/ex50-dal-interface.md for the interaction model and
  docs/runbooks/garage-relocation-cutover.md (Checkpoint C) for context.

  DAL config-mode syntax (verified on-device, firmware 25.11.10.42): there is
  NO `set` verb — a scalar is assigned by typing its element path followed by
  the value (e.g. `network interface modem enable false`), exactly as it reads
  back in `show config`. `add`/`del`/`move` operate on list elements. IPv4
  interface addressing is a single CIDR leaf (`address 10.0.0.1/24`) — there is
  no separate netmask leaf. Every human note lives in a Jinja comment (never
  rendered), so nothing here reaches the CLI as a stray line.

  Idempotency: assigning an already-current value is a no-op; `del` of an
  already-absent node returns a benign `# ERROR` for that one line without
  aborting the session (each line executes independently), and `save` still
  commits the rest. Safe to re-apply.

  ⚠ APPLY SAFELY — this delta makes the EX50 the 10.0.0.1 gateway and enables
  its DHCP server. If the EX50's LAN port shares the live 10.0.0.0/24 while you
  `save`, you create a DUPLICATE 10.0.0.1 and a ROGUE DHCP server on the
  production LAN (an ARP war for the gateway). Only apply the LAN/DHCP change
  either (a) on a LAN-ISOLATED bench, or (b) at the cutover instant with the
  upstream Xfinity gateway already in bridge mode (so it has vacated 10.0.0.1).
  Unplugging only the WAN is NOT sufficient — the hazard is on the LAN side.

  This delta contains NO secrets — SSH is key-auth (already enrolled) and the
  EX50's own WiFi radios are turned OFF here (the Aerohive APs serve WiFi). So
  this file is safe to commit as-is; nothing is redacted.
#}
config
{# --- LAN: platform gateway on the flat 10.0.0.0/24 (replaces Xfinity's .1).
   Single CIDR leaf — address+prefix together, no separate netmask. --- #}
network interface lan ipv4 address {{ ex50_lan_ip }}/{{ ex50_lan_prefix }}
{# --- DHCP server for non-static clients. The range is expressed as host
   octets within the LAN subnet; carved to exclude every OS-static (#80).
   Clients are handed 10.0.0.1 as gateway + resolver automatically (the
   dhcp_server `advanced` gateway/primary_dns default to `auto`). Verify the
   read-back shows lease_start {{ ex50_dhcp_pool_start.split('.')[-1] }} /
   lease_end {{ ex50_dhcp_pool_end.split('.')[-1] }}. --- #}
network interface lan ipv4 dhcp_server enable true
network interface lan ipv4 dhcp_server lease_start {{ ex50_dhcp_pool_start.split('.')[-1] }}
network interface lan ipv4 dhcp_server lease_end {{ ex50_dhcp_pool_end.split('.')[-1] }}
{# --- Hardening: drop the permissive "Allow all for testing" rule
   (firewall filter 2 on the bench unit) before the box fronts anything. --- #}
del firewall filter 2
{# --- Hardening: disable the (empty, ex-carrier) cellular modem at both layers
   so it stops the futile SIM-slot probing. --- #}
network interface modem enable false
network modem modem enable false
{# --- Turn the EX50's own WiFi OFF — the Aerohive APs serve house WiFi, and
   the factory config leaves digi_ap1 broadcasting a stray SSID. --- #}
network wifi ap digi_ap1 enable false
{# --- Enable NTP (syncs once the WAN reaches the internet at cutover). --- #}
service ntp enable true
{#
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  MANUAL, DO ON THE BENCH — SSH ACL hardening (NOT emitted here on purpose)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The bench `service ssh acl` includes the `wan` zone → SSH would be exposed
  on the public IP once Xfinity is bridged. Restrict it to the LAN/internal
  zone. Getting the list edit wrong over the very SSH session you're applying
  from risks a lock-out, so do this interactively (`ssh -tt`) on the bench and
  confirm the leaf path first:
      config ; show service ssh acl        # inspect current zones
      del service ssh acl interface end "wan"   # drop the wan zone
      save
  Gate: from OUTSIDE, `ssh admin@<public-ip>` MUST fail after cutover.
  Tracked in the cutover runbook's Checkpoint C hardening step.

  Also optional (not required for the flat cutover): pin DNS forwarder
  upstreams to {{ ex50_dns_upstreams | join(', ') }} instead of the
  WAN-provided resolvers — confirm the `network dns` / `service dns` leaf on
  the bench before adding.
#}
save
exit
